    "content": "Jump to content From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia Israeli computer scientist (1958–2019) Judit Bar-Ilan יהודית בר-אילן Born 1958 (1958) Died 2019 (aged 60–61) Alma mater Hebrew University of Jerusalem (BS, MS, PhD) Known for Research in informetrics, scientometrics, information retrieval, and web search engines Awards Derek de Solla Price Memorial Medal, Research in Information Science Award Scientific career Fields Information science, Informatics, Scientometrics Institutions Bar-Ilan University Doctoral advisor Michael O. Rabin, Michael Ben-Or Judit Bar-Ilan (Hebrew: יהודית בר-אילן, 1958–2019) was an Israeli computer scientist known for her research in informetrics and scientometrics. She was a professor of information science, and head of the Department of Information Science at Bar-Ilan University.[1] Education and career [edit] Bar-Ilan was born in 1958.[2] She was a student at the Hebrew University of Jerusalem, where she earned a bachelor\u0027s degree in 1981, an education diploma in 1982, a master\u0027s degree in 1983 and a Ph.D. in 1990.[3] Her dissertation, Applications of One-Way Functions and Randomization in Security Protocols, was jointly supervised by Michael O. Rabin and Michael Ben-Or.[4] After working for a year as a visiting lecturer at the University of Haifa, Bar-Ilan returned to the Hebrew University as an external teacher and later teaching fellow and teacher in library, archive and information studies. She joined the Bar-Ilan University Department of Information Science in 2002, where she was head of department from 2008 to 2012 and was promoted to full professor in 2010.[3] Contributions [edit] Bar-Ilan did important work early in her career in the fault tolerance of distributed computing,[1] and her dissertation research was in cryptography.[4] However, she is best known for her research on informetrics, scientometrics, information retrieval, and web search engines. Her interest in these topics stemmed from her work in the early 1990s on applications of distributed computing in library science. This work led her to perform important studies in the late 1990s on the accuracy, reliability, and stability over time of search engine results, and on the ability of search engines to handle non-English queries. She also used search engine results to study the link structure of the web, and applied methodologies including content analysis, user surveys, and user studies in these areas. Later in her career, her interests shifted to scientometrics, including citation analysis and studies of the h-index as well as altmetrics for measuring scholarly productivity. She also investigated the patterns of politically motivated internet activity.[1] Recognition [edit] The International Society for Scientometrics and Informetrics gave Bar-Ilan their Derek de Solla Price Memorial Medal in 2017, \"for her distinguished contribution to the field of scientometrics\".[2][5] The Association for Information Science and Technology gave her their Research in Information Science Award in 2018, for \"sustained contributions to informetrics, bibliometrics information retrieval, and most recently altmetrics, domains at the core of information science\".[2][6] A special memorial issue dedicated to Judit Bar-Ilan was published in the journal Scientometrics in June 2020.[7] Personal life [edit] Bar-Ilan died on July 16, 2019.[2] References [edit] ^ a b c Thelwall, Mike (October 2017), \"Judit Bar-Ilan: information scientist, computer scientist, scientometrician\", Scientometrics, 113 (3): 1235–1244, doi:10.1007/s11192-017-2551-3, S2CID 32600803 ^ a b c d Death of Professor Judit Bar-Ilan, iSchools, July 17, 2019 ^ a b Prof. Bar-Ilan Judit, Bar-Ilan University, retrieved 2019-07-17 ^ a b Judit Bar-Ilan at the Mathematics Genealogy Project ^ \"Judit Bar-Ilan wins the 2017 Derek John de Solla Price Medal\", Scientometrics, 113 (3): 1233–1234, October 2017, doi:10.1007/s11192-017-2552-2, S2CID 12179027 ^ Middleton, Lydia (August 8, 2018), Bar-Ilan Wins Research Award, Association for Information Science and Technology ^ \"Special Issue: Judit Bar-Ilan Memorial Issue\", Scientometrics, 123 (3), June 2020 External links [edit] Judit Bar-Ilan publications indexed by Google Scholar Authority control databases International ISNI VIAF WorldCat National United States Israel Academics ORCID Mathematics Genealogy Project ResearcherID Scopus zbMATH Google Scholar DBLP Publons Retrieved from \"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title\u003dJudit_Bar-Ilan\u0026oldid\u003d1288190042\" Categories: 1958 births 2019 deaths Hebrew University of Jerusalem alumni Academic staff of the Hebrew University of Jerusalem Academic staff of Bar-Ilan University Israeli women computer scientists Israeli computer scientists Burials at Har HaMenuchot Hidden categories: Articles with short description Short description is different from Wikidata Pages where birth or death is being automatically determined Articles with hCards Pages using infobox person with deprecated parameters Ar",
