    "content": "Jump to content From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia (Redirected from TechTarget) American business-to-business media company TechTarget, Inc. Trade name Informa TechTaget Company type Public Traded as Nasdaq: TTGT Russell 2000 component Industry Marketing Predecessor UBM Technology Group (1971–2018) Founded 1999; 26 years ago (1999) Headquarters Newton, Massachusetts Products Digital marketing Parent Informa (57%) Website techtarget.com TechTarget, Inc. (doing business as Informa TechTarget) is an American company that offers data-driven marketing services to business-to-business technology vendors.[1] TechTarget, Inc. was founded in 1999; it is headquartered in Newton, Massachusetts, with offices in London, Munich, Paris, San Francisco, Singapore and Sydney. History [edit] TechTarget was founded in 1999 by Greg Strakosch and Don Hawk as a spin-off of United Communications Group (UCG), the owner of Oil Price Information Service. In 2001, the company was recognized by B2B magazine on their Media Power 50 list.[2] In 2005, AdAge named CEO Greg Strakosch a Top 25 Newsmaker.[3] In 2016, TechTarget named Michael Cotoia as CEO and board member, and elected Greg Stakosch as executive chairman.[4] The company had an initial public offering in May 2007, being listed on the NASDAQ exchange with the symbol TTGT.[5] As of 2025, TechTarget\u0027s board of directors is chaired by Mary McDowell, an American technology executive.[6] Since launch, the company has made several acquisitions aimed at building its technology content reach: In 2003, TechTarget acquired Information Security Magazine.[7] In 2004, the company acquired publications including: Bitpipe.com,[8] TheServerSide.com and TheServerSide.net.[9] In 2007 (the year the company went public), TechTarget acquired KnowledgeStorm for $58 million.[10] In 2008, TechTarget acquired BrianMadden.com and BriForum.[11] The company acquired LeMagIT[12] and opened local operations in France. In 2011, it made a significant acquisition[13] of UK-based Computer Weekly, which had been published as a weekly print magazine by Reed Business Information for more than 45 years. The company launched its current purchase intent data services (IT Deal Alert) for technology vendors in 2014; the company has since added to the portfolio with a product called Priority Engine.[14] In 2020, TechTarget acquired the technology webinar company BrightTALK.[15] In late 2020, the firm also announced the acquisition of IT analyst firm Enterprise Strategy Group.[16] In 2021, TechTarget announced the acquisition of Xtelligent Healthcare Media, a marketing services, media, and data company.[17] TechTarget announced in 2024 that it would merge with the digital business of Informa\u0027s Informa Tech division. The resulting company would retain the TechTarget name; Informa would hold a 57% stake in the merged company, and existing TechTarget shareholders would hold a 43% stake.[18][19] The CEO of Informa Tech, Gary Nugent, would serve as CEO for the merged company. The planned merger was completed in December 2024, with the resulting company being known as Informa TechTarget.[20] References [edit] ^ \"TTGT\". Nasdaq.com. ^ B2B Magazine on the Media Power 50 list ^ AdAge named CEO Greg Strakosch a Top 25 Newsmaker ^ TechTarget named Michael Cotoia as CEO and board member, and elected Greg Stakosch as executive chairman ^ \"Prospectus\". US Securities and Exchange Commission. May 16, 2007. Retrieved November 7, 2016. ^ \"Leadership\". Informa TechTarget. 2020-04-01. Retrieved 2025-05-03. ^ acquired Information Security Magazine ^ publications including: Bitpipe.com ^ TheServerSide.com and TheServerSide.net ^ acquired KnowledgeStorm for $58 million ^ Techtarget buys Brian Madded company cbsnews.com ^ Techtarget acquired LeMagIT yahoo.com ^ TechTarget buys RBIS Computer Weekly foliomag.com ^ Priority Engine ^ \"TechTarget Acquires Enterprise Strategy Group (ESG), a Leading Provider of Decision-Support Content for Enterprise Tech Buyers and Sellers\". TechTarget. 4 January 2021. Retrieved 2021-02-22. ^ \"TechTarget Acquires Enterprise Strategy Group (ESG), a Leading Provider of Decision-Support Content for Enterprise Tech Buyers and Sellers\". TechTarget. 4 January 2021. Retrieved 2021-02-22. ^ \"TechTarget Acquires Xtelligent Healthcare Media, the Largest Marketing Services, Media and Data Company in B2B Healthcare Technology\". TechTarget. 4 August 2021. Retrieved 2023-12-06. ^ Knolle, Sharon (2024-09-02). \"Paramount Sells VidCon Creator Conference to UK Firm Informa\". TheWrap. Retrieved 2024-10-13. ^ \"TechTarget to Expand Scale and Leadership Position in B2B Data and Market Access through Strategic Combination with Informa Tech\u0027s Digital Businesses\" (Press release). Newton, Massachusetts: TechTarget. Business Wire. January 10, 2024. Retrieved 2024-10-13. ^ \"Informa TechTarget…scale in B2B Digital Services\" (PDF) (Press release). London, United Kingdom: Informa. December 3, 2024. Retrieved December 17, 2024. External links [edi",
